RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 6, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUNNINGS TALE stalked PARTY POLICE while racing two-wide, moved up to take the lead from that one at the eighth pole and then was all out to prevail. COCOA CENTS was reserved off the early pace, rallied three-wide into the stretch and closed strongly. WARREN'S MEMORABLE was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and finished fast. PARTY POLICE saved ground setting the pace to the eighth pole and weakened. TYCHE AWAITS YOU saved ground while being allowed to settle but lacked a rally when called upon. JACANA dropped back early came two-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Tyche Awaits You
ENTRY.OWNER: Crowe Shelly M and Richards Jay

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WITHEE was prominently placed from the outset, raced three-wide on the turn, was brushed by MOONLIGHTNWINE leaving the three-sixteenths pole, then came out near the wire to brush with that one again while being up in the final sixteenth to prevail narrowly. MOONLIGHTNWINE was allowed to settle in stride, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole, came in to brush with the winner leaving the three-sixteenths pole and finished strongly to just miss after brushing with winner again near the wire. THE THIRD RING saved ground prompting CONTEJAS into the stretch and finished well for third in a steady effort. CONTEJAS set the pressured pace to deep stretch while racing two-wide and weakened late. VALIDATE was unhurried early, swung out to come five-wide into the stretch and gained his best stride too late. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE ACTIONS OF WITHEE AND MOONLIGHTNWINE BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS RULED THERE WAS MUTUAL INTERFERENCE AND MADE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: The Third Ring
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, saved ground, steady effort

ENTRY.NAME: Moonlightnwine
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 4-wide 1/4, came in brushed 3/16, brushed late, missed

CAPIAT was off a step slow to get away behind the field then was unhurried, came five-wide into the stretch and was gaining late. CHARLIE'S MAN saved ground while being allowed to settle but lacked a rally when asked. WESTERBERG bobbled shortly after the start, then moved up to be forwardly placed while three-wide, came four-wide into the stretch and weakened. MY DAD IS THIRSTY was four-wide on the first turn, then raced three to four-wide the rest of the way and failed to threaten.
